        "heading_e4LJYq": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "The Raw Japanese Denim",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_JbjHCQ": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>For Edition 07, we selected raw Japanese denim from Kojima — a region long associated with some of the most respected denim mills in the world.</strong><br/>Woven on traditional shuttle looms, the fabric develops a dense, slightly irregular texture with natural depth.<br/>What defines this denim is its character.<br/>Structured at first, it gradually softens — adapting to the movements of its owner. Because it is raw, it evolves. Creases form. Fades appear.<br/>The surface is shaped by wear, not by artificial treatment.<br/>We choose it for one reason: when a garment is meant to last and become personal, the fabric must offer more than appearance.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
